<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:planet="http://planet.intertwingly.net/"><id>tag:typepad.com,2003:post-6a00d83452383469e2022ad37859e2200c</id><link href="https://3dpancakes.typepad.com/ernie/2018/11/toronto-is-hiring-in-computational-geometry.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><link href="https://3dpancakes.typepad.com/ernie/2018/11/toronto-is-hiring-in-computational-geometry.html" rel="replies" type="text/html"/><title>Toronto is hiring in computational geometry</title><summary>Toronto's Computer Science Department is searching for new tenure-track faculty in computational geometry. Apply at https://academicjobsonline.org/ajo/jobs/11954 by November 15!<div class="commentbar"><p/><a href="https://3dpancakes.typepad.com/ernie/2018/11/toronto-is-hiring-in-computational-geometry.html"><img class="commenticon" src="/images/post-icon.png"/> Post a comment</a></div></summary><content type="xhtml" xml:lang="en-US"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><div><div>Toronto's Computer Science Department is searching for new tenure-track faculty in computational geometry. Apply by November 15!</div>
<blockquote><p><small>The Faculty of Arts and Science at the University of Toronto invites applications for up to three tenure-stream appointments in the <a href="https://web.cs.toronto.edu/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Department of Computer Science</a> in the areas of Knowledge Representation and Reasoning, Computer Systems, and <strong>Computational Geometry</strong>. The appointment(s) will be at the rank of Assistant Professor and will commence July 1, 2019.</small></p>
<p><small>Candidates in all areas of Computer Science that touch upon knowledge representation and reasoning, computer systems, and <strong>computational geometry in the broadest possible sense</strong> will be considered. We are especially interested in exceptional candidates who transcend traditional computing research topics and complement our <a href="https://web.cs.toronto.edu/people/faculty.htm">existing strengths</a>....</small></p>
<p><small>Application material for the position should be submitted online through AcademicJobsOnline at <a href="https://academicjobsonline.org/ajo/jobs/11954" title="https://academicjobsonline.org/ajo/jobs/11954">https://academicjobsonline.org/ajo/jobs/11954</a>. It should include the candidate’s curriculum vitae, a list of publications, a research statement, a teaching statement, and at least three letters of reference (on letterhead, signed and scanned) uploaded to AcademicJobsOnline directly by the writers. Review of applications will begin on <strong>November 15, 2018</strong> and applicants should endeavor to have all materials submitted by then, however applications will be accepted until the position is filled.</small></p>
</blockquote></div></div></content><updated planet:format="November 06, 2018 05:41 PM">2018-11-06T17:41:10Z</updated><published planet:format="November 06, 2018 05:41 PM">2018-11-06T17:41:10Z</published><category term="Academia"/><category term="Computational Geometry"/><author><name>Jeff Erickson</name></author><source><id>tag:typepad.com,2003:weblog-6686</id><link href="https://3dpancakes.typepad.com/ernie/atom.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://3dpancakes.typepad.com/ernie/" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><subtitle>Let Σ be a combinatorial surface with n vertices, genus g, and b boundaries.  Amen.</subtitle><title>Ernie's 3D Pancakes</title><updated planet:format="November 06, 2018 05:41 PM">2018-11-06T17:41:10Z</updated><planet:format>atom10</planet:format><planet:http_location>https://3dpancakes.typepad.com/ernie/atom.xml</planet:http_location><planet:module>toc</planet:module><planet:items_per_page>40</planet:items_per_page><planet:face>erickson.jpeg</planet:face><planet:name>Ernie's 3D Pancakes</planet:name><planet:css-id>ernie-s-3d-pancakes</planet:css-id><planet:bozo>false</planet:bozo><planet:http_last_modified>Tue, 06 Nov 2018 17:41:43 GMT</planet:http_last_modified><planet:http_status>301</planet:http_status></source></entry>
